statement:
Now find the general solution of the nonhomogenous system (with matrix
$A$ as above):

\begin{align*}\vec{x}' = A \vec{x} +  \left[ \begin{array}{c} 25 e^{3t} \\ 0 \end{array} \right]\end{align*}

\emph{Hint: to find a particular solution, you may use either the method
of variation of parameters, or the method of undetermined coefficients;
for the latter, try
$\vec{x}_p(t) = \left[ \begin{array}{c} (at + b)e^{3t} \\ (ct+d)e^{3t} \end{array} \right]$}
